# Â§Doc-only â€” seal-cap rejection error name (Sealed â€” four-state/merge-outcome pass)
# ============================================================================
# The seal-cap rejection is Sealed (an INERT below-seal parent that changes
# nothing: parent.serial < seal_serial) â€” renamed from SiblingLocked (and earlier
# ParentLocked) at the four-state / formalized-merge-outcome pass. Not every
# below-seal parent is Sealed: a parent AT the seal (parent_serial == seal_serial)
# extends cleanly, and a sibling at the seal's own serial (parent v_{seal-1},
# parent_serial == seal_serial - 1) forms a live fork (Forked / Disputed),
# retained â€” not Sealed. The cap bounds content extended FROM the seal; Sealed is
# the inert below-seal parent â€” not a "locked parent," and not a sibling to the seal.

