#     truly-dead kels synthetics stay banned. vdti's first-seen effective-SAID is:
#     a single confirmed tip â†’ its real SAID; NO single tip â†’ a type-tagged
#     `synthetic` marker recoupled to the verdict (forked: / disputed:), qualified
#     by prefix + position, NOT a digest over the competing tips (adversarially
#     extensible â†’ flood-unstable, deleted). So the verdict-recoupled colon forms
#     forked: / disputed: are LIVE (the synthetic value on a no-single-tip chain);
#     bare "divergent" / "irreconcilable" and the "forked"/"disputed" verdict words
